    • Camp

      public Camp()
      Constructor for a new camp, used when staff is creating a new camp.

    • Camp

      private Camp(UUID campId, String campName, Date[] dates, Date closingDate, GroupName userGroup, String location, int totalSlots, int committeeSlot, String description, boolean visibility, Staff createdBy, ArrayList<CampMember> attendees, ArrayList<CampMember> committees, ArrayList<Enquiry> enquiries, ArrayList<Suggestion> suggestions)
      Constructor for Camp class, used to create a copy of the Camp.
      Parameters:
      campId - Unique identifier of the camp
      campName - Name of the camp.
      dates - Dates in which the camp is active.
      closingDate - Last day for registration.
      userGroup - Faculty in which the camp is open to.
      location - Location of the camp.
      totalSlots - Maximum number of slots for students to participate (including committees).
      committeeSlot - Maximum number of slots for commitee members.
      description - Description of the camp.
      visibility - Flag for Student's access to view the camp.
      createdBy - Staff who created the camp.
      attendees - ArrayList of CampMember with students attending the camp.
      committees - ArrayList of CampMember with students leading the camp.
      enquiries - ArrayList of Enquiry made for the camp.
      suggestions - ArrayList of Suggestion for the camp.
